-- Toulon Beats Ospreys in Heineken Cup Rugby; London Irish Top Munster
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-09T19:25:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/toulon-beats-ospreys-in-heineken-cup-rugby-london-irish-top-munster.html
Paul Sackey’s late try gave Toulon a
19-14 win over Ospreys in their opening game in rugby’s Heinken
Cup, while London Irish beat Munster 23-17.  Sackey touched down with four minutes remaining for the win
in Pool 3 of Europe’s top club competition. Ryan Lamb kicked 15
points in London Irish’s home win over two-time champ Munster in
the other Pool 3 match.  Cardiff Blues edged Edinburgh 18-17 in Pool 1; Leinster
defeated Racing Metro 38-22 and Clermont Auvergne beat Saracens
25-10 in Pool 2; and Leicester Tigers topped Benetton Treviso
34-29 and Scarlets outscored Perpignan 43-34 in Pool 5.  Toulouse opens its European title defense tomorrow against
London Wasps and Biarritz, last season’s runnerup, visits Bath.
In yesterday’s opening matches, Glasgow Warriors beat Newport
Gwent 21-13, Ulster routed Aironi 30-6 and Northampton Saints
topped Castres 18-14.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
